1
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:39,260
Mast! Lay down the mast!

2
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:46,900
Hurry up and get the rope!

3
00:00:48,220 --> 00:00:50,900
Bow and stern face the banks! Quick!

4
00:00:54,580 --> 00:00:56,980
Thousands of homes are brightly lit,

5
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:59,420
and the doors to them are wide open.

6
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:01,580
This is East Capital.

7
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:05,180
New wine from Sunyang Restaurant!

8
00:01:05,180 --> 00:01:07,700
Welcome to enjoy it!

9
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:10,380
If you want to know what happens next,

10
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:12,460
wait until next time.

11
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:14,980
People from all over the world gather here,

12
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:17,940
and envoys from various countries come to communicate with the authorities.

13
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:24,660
[Riverside Code at Qingming Festival]

14
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:26,660
[Adapted from Ye Wenbiao's Novel Series of the Same Name]

15
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:27,980
[Episode 23]

16
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:28,680
[There are 3 types of deceit: deceiving for profit, which deserves punishment,]

17
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,180
[deceiving out of fear of punishment, which may be forgiven, and unintentional]

18
00:01:29,180 --> 00:01:29,980
[deceit, which needs closer examination. - Cheng Hao from Northern Song Dynasty]

19
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:53,380
Mo.

20
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,170
Sorry,

21
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,370
I had too much on my plate and came late.

22
00:01:57,370 --> 00:01:57,840
It's okay.

23
00:02:00,270 --> 00:02:01,830
I asked you out last minute.

24
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,230
Have some tea first.

25
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:05,080
Zheng,

26
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:06,680
do you have something to say?

27
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,160
No,

28
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,270
I just feel like you're always too busy

29
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:12,190
and probably don't take care of yourself.

30
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,240
From now on,

31
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,800
you should come home for meals.

32
00:02:16,550 --> 00:02:17,440
It's fine.

33
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,720
The Office of Justice has a public kitchen.

34
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,470
But the food from the kitchen

35
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,630
is no match for our sister's cooking.

36
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,110
Actually, I am wondering

37
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,210
is it because I moved in

38
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,930
and caused trouble for everyone

39
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,360
that you don't want to stay home?

40
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,830
No, Zheng.

41
00:02:41,910 --> 00:02:42,600
Really, no.

42
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:47,360
Oh, right.

43
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:49,890
This is for you.

44
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:52,520
I found it while packing my things.

45
00:02:58,670 --> 00:03:00,550
I took it from home when our family

46
00:03:00,550 --> 00:03:01,830
fell into misfortune.

47
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:04,440
I've kept it close all these years.

48
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,730
You love clever objects,

49
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:07,940
so I'm giving this to you,

50
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:09,500
meaning it's somewhere where it can be a value.

51
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,360
This is...

52
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,390
a ship blueprint?

53
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:14,170
Yes.

54
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:17,910
My father was the chief shipbuilder at the Taihu Shipyard.

55
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:20,320
He handed

56
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:23,440
this blueprint to me personally before he passed.

57
00:03:28,190 --> 00:03:28,960
Zheng,

58
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,960
this is too valuable.

59
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,160
I can't accept it.

60
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:33,390
No, Mo!

61
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,190
Now I'm with all of you,

62
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,050
and I have this family.

63
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:36,920
I cherish it greatly.

64
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:39,750
It's time for me to let go of these things.

65
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:45,670
Zheng,

66
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,600
you are Wen Yue's family,

67
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,830
so you're our family too.

68
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,030
Don't worry.

69
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,830
I'll keep this blueprint safe.

70
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,000
Then,

71
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,000
let's toast with tea instead of wine.

72
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:57,800
Sure.

73
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,470
Why not have dinner at home tonight?

74
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,190
What would you like to eat?

75
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,360
I'll pick it up on my way back.

76
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:12,750
Alright.

77
00:04:16,390 --> 00:04:16,880
By the way,

78
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:18,200
don't tell my sister

79
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,550
about the blueprint.

80
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:20,950
I'm afraid it'll upset her.

81
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:25,000
First, heat the oil.

82
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:29,920
You need ginger to stir-fry chicken,

83
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,320
so it wonâ€™t have a greasy smell.

84
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:34,830
Put it into the wok!

85
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,230
Water, pour it in!

86
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:38,320
Pour it all?

87
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:38,830
All of it!

88
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,270
Cover the lid.

89
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:44,390
Ban,

90
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,670
do you need help with anything?

91
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,600
I'm done.

92
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,830
Take it to Wen Yue.

93
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,440
Ban,

94
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,000
go find Father and bring him back for dinner.

95
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,760
Got it!

96
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:57,480
Zhao Ban,

97
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,790
where are you going?

98
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:02,480
Zhao Mo! A surprise seeing you here.

99
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:04,040
I'm going to find Father.

100
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:04,720
Alright, off I go.

101
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,830
Mo's back!

102
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,200
Wen Yue, Buyou,

103
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:08,640
Zheng.

104
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,390
This is custard from the Office of Justice's kitchen.

105
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:14,720
You're just like your big brother.

106
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,200
You have my style!

107
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,160
Did you come back today because you knew

108
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,880
the imperial chef cooked himself?

109
00:05:21,830 --> 00:05:23,510
Your cooking is getting more delicious.

110
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,600
I'm going to grab some clean clothes.

111
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,600
Go ahead.

112
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,390
What did he say he's getting?

113
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,040
Some clean clothes.

114
00:05:31,830 --> 00:05:32,600
Dear,

115
00:05:32,830 --> 00:05:34,200
help me stir the chicken.

116
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:39,480
Why did he come back so suddenly?

117
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:41,730
Let's add another dish for Mo.

118
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:53,350
Mo,

119
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:55,520
is there something special you'd like to eat?

120
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,770
Tell Wen Yue, and she'll make it for you.

121
00:05:57,140 --> 00:05:57,900
Got it.

122
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,000
Is it cold

123
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:00,670
sleeping over at the office?

124
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:01,760
No, not at all.

125
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:04,550
Since Zheng came back,

126
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:05,720
he's been using your bed.

127
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,550
I'm feeling sorry about it.

128
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,200
I want to discuss something with you.

129
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:10,550
Look, Mo,

130
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,760
let's push this rack out

131
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:14,550
and place your bed here.

132
00:06:14,670 --> 00:06:15,760
I'll add another board to make it wider...

133
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,070
Buyou, no need.

134
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:18,510
Once we move to the new house,

135
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,510
there'll be more space.

136
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,270
Okay.

137
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,200
When we get the new house,

138
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:26,230
I will give you the biggest room!

139
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:29,160
By the way,

140
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,550
I want to ask you something.

141
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:32,880
Was the old shipyard of Wen Yue's family

142
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:35,230
a private one or a government-run one?

143
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,550
A private one, I think.

144
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,960
Why are you asking about this?

145
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:40,940
A private shipyard?

146
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:45,480
What's the matter?

147
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:52,480
Come on.

148
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:53,830
Sit over here.

149
00:06:58,950 --> 00:06:59,760
Buyou,

150
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,920
look at this blueprint.

151
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:03,950
Is it for a warship or a private ship?

152
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:06,880
I don't know how to tell.

153
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:08,000
How can you distinguish it?

154
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:10,000
This is a modification blueprint.

155
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:12,480
The ship has several rows of oars.

156
00:07:12,790 --> 00:07:14,200
This is obviously a warship.

157
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:15,600
But

158
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,000
why would a private shipyard

159
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,670
have a blueprint for a warship?

160
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:20,880
Are you saying

161
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:21,790
this blueprint

162
00:07:21,790 --> 00:07:22,950
is from Wen Yue's family?

163
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:25,160
Zheng said this blueprint

164
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,350
was handed to him by his father before he passed.

165
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,040
It's from their shipyard.

166
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,790
What else did he say?

167
00:07:38,510 --> 00:07:40,790
He said he knew I was interested in these things,

168
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,600
and he didn't want to keep them

169
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,510
because they reminded him of sad memories.

170
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:45,720
So he gave it to me.

171
00:07:47,950 --> 00:07:49,160
Did Wen Yue see it?

172
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,440
No.

173
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,350
Right.

174
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,390
It's all in the past.

175
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:56,640
Don't tell her.

176
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:58,640
I'm afraid it'll upset her.

177
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,830
I understand.

178
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,720
Zheng also explicitly told me

179
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,760
not to let Wen Yue know about this.

180
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:08,110
I'll take the ship blueprint and study it.

181
00:08:09,550 --> 00:08:10,350
Time to eat.

182
00:08:13,550 --> 00:08:14,390
Oh, you're cooking.

183
00:08:14,670 --> 00:08:16,760
Inspector Gu, you arrive just in time for dinner.

184
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:18,760
Gu,

185
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,440
you knew we were about to eat,

186
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,480
so you came over!

187
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,070
Mr. Gu is here!

188
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,600
Mo,

189
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,440
go help bring out the dishes.

190
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,000
Alright.

191
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:29,510
Zhao,

192
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,350
Zou Mian may already be in East Capital.

193
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:36,110
Wasn't Zou Mian in the South?

194
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,550
In the past two days,

195
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:41,520
some high-ranking officials were accused of taking bribes,

196
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,790
rumored to be as much as 300,000 liang of silver.

197
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,590
They've all been taken in for questioning.

198
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,470
This includes officials from the Ministry of Justice,

199
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:48,780
the Office of Justice,

200
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:50,320
and our Kaifeng Court.

201
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:52,280
They're all responsible for handling criminal cases.

202
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:54,710
All of them are connected to Luan Hui's case.

203
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,470
That old scoundrel Zou Mian

204
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,080
must be here to save his son-in-law and daughter.

205
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,590
It's said that he's gravely ill in the South,

206
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,400
but I suspect

207
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,880
he's already slipped

208
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,000
into East Capital unnoticed.

209
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:15,470
What's wrong?

210
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,120
It's possible.

211
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,720
Something on your mind?

212
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:23,800
No, I'm listening.

213
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:27,910
Mo,

214
00:09:28,710 --> 00:09:29,250
where's Zheng?

215
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,520
He was just here.

216
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,230
Getting ready for dinner.

217
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,790
- Zheng, come out for dinner! - Let's eat first.

218
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:35,550
We'll talk after dinner.

219
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:38,350
Mo,

220
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:39,910
hurry, bring some wine over.

221
00:09:39,910 --> 00:09:41,080
I must have come at a bad time.

222
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,670
You all go ahead and eat.

223
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:42,590
Have you eaten?

224
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,350
I'll catch up with you later, Gu.

225
00:09:50,710 --> 00:09:51,960
Xie Laoba

226
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,910
keeps asking me to drink away his sorrows.

227
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,580
Every time he drinks, he'll cries,

228
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,760
loud enough

229
00:09:56,790 --> 00:09:57,880
for all of Sparrow Lane to hear.

230
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,880
- People even think I'm bullying him... - Alright, Father.

231
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,910
Father, you're back!

232
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:01,640
We're back!

233
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,520
I'm back!

234
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,670
Let's eat first, Father.

235
00:10:04,670 --> 00:10:06,080
Go out after dinner.

236
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,230
What's for dinner today?

237
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:08,910
Today...

238
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:09,840
we're having stir-fried chicken.

239
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:10,910
Have a seat, Father.

240
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:11,840
Where's Zheng?

241
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,710
He's still in the room.

242
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:15,200
Zheng, come out for dinner!

243
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,110
I'll tell you...

244
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:16,790
Mrs. Lan...

245
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:18,280
- Coming! - She doesn't side with me at all.

246
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,280
- I know exactly where she's gone. - Uncle.

247
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:21,200
Ban.

248
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,080
Come on, dinner time!

249
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,710
Time to eat.

250
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,080
Now that Mo's back,

251
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:28,000
Uncle and Buyou should have a drink, shouldn't you?

252
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,010
Not today.

253
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:31,880
I'll drink.

254
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:35,030
It's all yours.

255
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:36,640
No way.

256
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,880
- That's too much. - That's too much for him!

257
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,230
This is mine.

258
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,000
All mine!

259
00:10:44,470 --> 00:10:44,910
Mo.

260
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:47,120
- You're not eating, just drinking? - Father.

261
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:47,960
Have a bite first.

262
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:52,470
Here.

263
00:10:56,110 --> 00:10:56,910
Buyou,

264
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,110
this bowl of wine

265
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,640
is to thank you for taking me in,

266
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,760
and thank Mo for being so understanding.

267
00:11:03,110 --> 00:11:05,230
You've given me such a wonderful family.

268
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,910
So,

269
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:08,280
I toast to you all.

270
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:13,470
I...

271
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:15,000
Zheng,

272
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:16,350
you're being too kind.

273
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,880
Buyou and I

274
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,000
will down this drink together.

275
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,910
Don't force yourself.

276
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:29,000
It's fine.

277
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:31,790
It's rare for Zheng to be in such good spirits.

278
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:35,790
I'm happy to have you with us.

279
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:36,590
Come on.

280
00:11:42,710 --> 00:11:43,620
Buyou, you're so bold!

281
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:45,900
Buyou,

282
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,080
let me refill your bowl.

283
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,320
- This is really good. - You all eat something first.

284
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,320
Alright, it's fine.

285
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,000
Mo.

286
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,520
